    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1867777179" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14775930124886324258">Very interesting read on what should* have been done during the Cold War in Southeast Asia. Lederer and Burdick managed to pen something that was both enjoyable and fictional yet based in historical fact. There are a lot of characters to keep an eye on, which is something my professor mentioned beforehand. The story manages to be tongue-in-cheek and critical while also offering characters the reader can root for. It really does live up to its name as the synonym for everything wrong with America</span>
  <span id="freeText14775930124886324258" style="display:none">Very interesting read on what should* have been done during the Cold War in Southeast Asia. Lederer and Burdick managed to pen something that was both enjoyable and fictional yet based in historical fact. There are a lot of characters to keep an eye on, which is something my professor mentioned beforehand. The story manages to be tongue-in-cheek and critical while also offering characters the reader can root for. It really does live up to its name as the synonym for everything wrong with American foreign policy. If you decide to read this, you better not skip the Factual Epilogue! If you do, you basically didn't read the book.<br /><br />*It's hard to say whether their suggestions would have been effective with better results or if they could have even been implemented so immediately.</span>
